Love The Way You Look & Feel

BUILD YOUR SELF CONFIDENCE

As you consider plastic surgery, remember the old adage that beauty is more than skin deep. The way you look is largely determined by the contours and dimensions of the bone structure that underlies the soft tissues. As we age, our skin elasticity decreases and the underlying soft tissues descend being affected by gravity giving us the aged appearance.
Dr. Michael Jones has dedicated his practice to natural appearing plastic surgery that rejuvenates the health and appearance while regaining the beauty that was once yours. Dr. Jones has helped men and women of all ages and walks of life turn back the clock and achieve a more youthful appearance by tailoring treatment to the patients’ individual attributes, ethnic features and desires. 

 


Facial Procedures 
 
Body Procedures


 
 
 


Your face is the first thing people notice about you. Whether it is your eyes, your smile or expressiveness you are constantly aware of the impression you make on other people. When wrinkles, skin discoloration, sagging skin or other evidence of aging become more noticeable, cosmetic surgery may be the answer.  With cosmetic surgery you can turn back the hands of time. Not only will you look and feel younger you will also feel more confident and vibrant.
 
Millions of people every New Year resolve to lose weight.  Some are successful, some are not. Even the most successful dieter have problems getting rid of as much fat as they would like. Some areas of their body do not respond to diet and exercise the way they would like them to. It comes as no surprise then, that some of the most common cosmetic plastic surgery procedures involve reshaping of the body through removal of excess fat deposits. Arms, abdomen, hips, thighs and knees respond very well to treatment.


 



