Scar & Keloid Treatments


Scar Revision

When the skin is in the process of recovering from an injury, whether the result of an accident, surgery, a burn, or acne, scarring will occur wherever multiple layers of the skin have been affected. Once a scar forms, it is permanent but may be made less visible or relocated surgically. With very few exceptions most people are self-conscious about facial scars. Some people may also experience diminished functioning of the eyes, mouth, or nose due to scarring. If you've wondered how facial scar revision could improve your appearance, your self-confidence, or your level of facial functioning, you need to know how scar revision works and what you can expect from this procedure.﻿﻿ 

  I didn’t think it was possible to remove my scar but Dr. Jones did an amazing job. – Patient CSV 


PROCEDURE
Scar revision is a surgical procedure to improve or reduce the appearance of scars. It also restores function and corrects disfigurement caused by an injury, wound or previous surgery.  Scars are formed when the skin is damaged in some way. Scars are permanent visible wounds and are unpredictable in their development.  Although a scar cannot be removed completely, Dr. Jones can improve the appearance of a scar by making them less noticeable.
 
METHOD
Many factors affect the severity of scarring including the size and depth of the wound, blood supply to the area, thickness and color of your skin, as well as the direction of the scar. If you are considering scar revision, it is important to consult with a board-certified plastic surgeon that can help you determine which procedure is best for you.
 
There are several treatment options which vary based on the type and degree of scarring, however, the Z-plasty is recommended. Z-plasty is a surgical technique that repositions a scar to more closely conform it to the natural lines and creases of the skin.
 
IDEAL CANDIDATE
The ideal candidate for scar revision surgery is a healthy individual of any age who would like to improve the appearance of scars anywhere on their body.  It is also beneficial if the candidate does not have active acne or other skin diseases in the area to be treated
 
RECOVERY / POSTOPERATIVE

Temporary discoloration or discomfort will occur in the first two weeks
Healing is expected to continue for several weeks
Dressings may be removed after one to two weeks post surgery
Minimal activity is advised post surgery
Use of scar products (i.e. Keloid Care) and massages to the affected area(s) are essential for individuals prone to thickened or keloid scars

 
BEFORE & AFTER IMAGES﻿ | BACK TO PROCEDURES  

 
 
 
 
 
 

Keloid Care

Keloid Care is an innovative, new fast-acting, topical cream specifically designed to help improve the appearance of thick or stubborn scars like keloids and hypertropic (raised) scar, as well as lighten any discoloration in affected and surrounding area(s).

The cream is carefully formulated with Beta Ionone, a powerful anti-oxidant shown to nourish the skin and help improve the appearance of thick, stubborn or hard to treat scars. Keloid Care also contains Aloe, Cocoa Butter, Shea Butter and other natural ingredients commonly used to soften and moisturize the skin. 

  "I first heard about Keloid Care when my daughter Marley hit her chin on the side of my table. I took her to Dr. Jones to get stitches and he stitched her up beautifully but I was still afraid that she was going to have a scar on her face for the rest of her life. He recommended Keloid Care and I applied it and it was barely visible after a few weeks. ~Yvonne Wright mother of Marley"



 
